---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Configuration - SQLift">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none">
      <h1>Configuration</h1>

      <h2>Configuration File</h2>
      <p>SQLift uses a YAML configuration file (sqlift.yaml) to customize its behavior. Here's a complete reference of available options:</p>

      <h3>Basic Configuration</h3>
      <pre><code>version: "1"
sql:
  engine: "postgresql"  # Database engine
  schema: "schema.sql" # Path to schema file
  output:
    package: "com.example.entity"
    directory: "src/main/java"</code></pre>

      <h3>Advanced Options</h3>
      <pre><code>version: "1"
sql:
  engine: "postgresql"
  schema: "schema.sql"
  output:
    package: "com.example.entity"
    directory: "src/main/java"
    options:
      lombok: true  # Enable Lombok annotations
      jpa:
        enabled: true
        type: "jakarta"  # or "javax"
      naming:
        class:
          strategy: "singular"  # Convert plural to singular
        field:
          strategy: "camelCase"  # Convert snake_case to camelCase
      generation:
        constructors:
          default: true
          allArgs: true
        methods:
          getters: true
          setters: true
          toString: true
          equals: true
          hashCode: true</code></pre>

      <h2>Configuration Options</h2>
      
      <h3>Database Engine</h3>
      <p>Supported values for sql.engine:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>postgresql (fully supported)</li>
        <li>mysql (planned)</li>
        <li>oracle (planned)</li>
        <li>sqlserver (planned)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>JPA Implementation</h3>
      <p>Choose between Jakarta EE and Java EE annotations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>jakarta - Uses jakarta.persistence.* packages</li>
        <li>javax - Uses javax.persistence.* packages</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Lombok Integration</h3>
      <p>When lombok: true is set, SQLift will:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Add @Data annotation for getters/setters</li>
        <li>Use @NoArgsConstructor for default constructor</li>
        <li>Use @AllArgsConstructor for all-args constructor</li>
        <li>Add @Builder for builder pattern support</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Environment Variables</h2>
      <p>SQLift also supports configuration through environment variables:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>SQLIFT_CONFIG - Path to configuration file</li>
        <li>SQLIFT_SCHEMA - Path to schema file</li>
        <li>SQLIFT_OUTPUT_DIR - Output directory</li>
        <li>SQLIFT_PACKAGE - Base package name</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>